In all cases, tables should:

- use brief but informative titles
- be numbered sequentially
- be positioned as close to the reference text as possible

Borders and shading can be used to:

- add colour and interest to a table
- help improve readability by grouping related information or by separating individual rows of data
- focus attention on key data by highlighting it

When referring to tables within the text, use the following formats depending on the context:

{% include guide_example.liquid title = "tables" content= "

- As shown in Table 2, users were more likely to choose tram travel
- The transport preferences of users are shown in Table 2
- All users responded positively to the proposed transport options(see Table 2)
- Most users preferred trams to buses, as shown in Table 2 " %}
